**Example: A Simple Form with Real-Time Data Saving**

Suppose we want to create a simple form that captures user input and saves it to a local storage solution. The form will have two fields: a text input field and a submit button.

**Design:**

The form will have the following design elements:

* A text input field with a label and a placeholder text
* A submit button with a label
* A real-time validation message that appears when the user submits the form with invalid input

**Implementation:**

To implement this form, we'll use the following code:
```javascript
// Get the form elements
const form = document.getElementById('myForm');
const inputField = document.getElementById('inputField');
const submitButton = document.getElementById('submitButton');
const validationMessage = document.getElementById('validationMessage');

// Set up event listeners
form.addEventListener('submit', handleSubmit);
inputField.addEventListener('input', handleInput);

// Function to handle form submission
function handleSubmit(event) {
  event.preventDefault();
  const inputValue = inputField.value.trim();
  if (inputValue === '') {
    validationMessage.textContent = 'Please enter a value';
    return;
  }
  // Save the input value to local storage
  localStorage.setItem('inputValue', inputValue);
  // Clear the input field
  inputField.value = '';
  // Update the validation message
  validationMessage.textContent = '';
}

// Function to handle input changes
function handleInput() {
  const inputValue = inputField.value.trim();
  if (inputValue === '') {
    validationMessage.textContent = 'Please enter a value';
  } else {
    validationMessage.textContent = '';
  }
}

// Function to update the validation message
function updateValidationMessage(message) {
  validationMessage.textContent = message;
}
```
**Real-Time Validation:**

To implement real-time validation, we'll use the following code:
```javascript
// Function to validate the input value
function validateInputValue(inputValue) {
  const pattern = /^[a-zA-Z0-9]+$/;
  if (pattern.test(inputValue)) {
    return true;
  }
  return false;
}

// Update the validation message based on the input value
function updateValidationMessage(inputValue) {
  if (validateInputValue(inputValue)) {
    validationMessage.textContent = '';
  } else {
    validationMessage.textContent = 'Invalid input';
  }
}
```
**Real-Time Data Saving:**

To implement real-time data saving, we'll use the following code:
```javascript
// Function to save the input value to local storage
function saveInputValue(inputValue) {
  localStorage.setItem('inputValue', inputValue);
}

// Update the input value in local storage when the form is submitted
function updateInputValueInLocalStorage(inputValue) {
  saveInputValue(inputValue);
}
```
**Putting it all together:**

To put all the code together, we'll create a single function that handles form submission, input changes, and validation:
```javascript
// Function to handle form submission, input changes, and validation
function handleFormSubmissionAndInputChanges() {
  // Get the form elements
  const form = document.getElementById('myForm');
  const inputField = document.getElementById('inputField');
  const submitButton = document.getElementById('submitButton');
  const validationMessage = document.getElementById('validationMessage');

  // Set up event listeners
  form.addEventListener('submit', handleSubmit);
  inputField.addEventListener('input', handleInput);

  // Function to handle form submission
  function handleSubmit(event) {
    event.preventDefault();
    const inputValue = inputField.value.trim();
    if (inputValue === '') {
      validationMessage.textContent = 'Please enter a value';
      return;
    }
    // Save the input value to local storage
    saveInputValue(inputValue);
    // Clear the input field
    inputField.value = '';
    // Update the validation message
    validationMessage.textContent = '';
  }

  // Function to handle input changes
  function handleInput() {
    const inputValue = inputField.value.trim();
    if (inputValue === '') {
      validationMessage.textContent = 'Please enter a value';
    } else {
      validationMessage.textContent = '';
    }
  }

  // Function to update the validation message
  function updateValidationMessage(message) {
    validationMessage.textContent = message;
  }

  // Function to validate the input value
  function validateInputValue(inputValue) {
    const pattern = /^[a-zA-Z0-9]+$/;
    if (pattern.test(inputValue)) {
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }

  // Function to save the input value to local storage
  function saveInputValue(inputValue) {
    localStorage.setItem('inputValue', inputValue);
  }

  // Update the input value in local storage when the form is submitted
  function updateInputValueInLocalStorage(inputValue) {
    saveInputValue(inputValue);
  }
}
```
This code demonstrates how to implement a simple form with real-time data saving using local storage. The form has two fields: a text input field and a submit button. When the user submits the form, the input value is saved to local storage. When the user changes the input value, the validation message is updated in real-time.

